\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Theme inheritance chain. Each layer overrides only what it declares; everything else falls through to the layer below. The project accent override is the outermost layer and applies only while Focus Mode is active; it is removed when the project is deactivated, restoring the user's configured accent. A Store theme that covers only the shell and GTK4 leaves Wine and Qt at the base theme.}}{68}{figure.caption.135}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:theme-chain}{{9}{68}{Theme inheritance chain. Each layer overrides only what it declares; everything else falls through to the layer below. The project accent override is the outermost layer and applies only while Focus Mode is active; it is removed when the project is deactivated, restoring the user's configured accent. A Store theme that covers only the shell and GTK4 leaves Wine and Qt at the base theme}{figure.caption.135}{}}
